  stimulus_text = 'The author of a recent book on the history of the American West wrote the following sentence: "As a result of the vast distances and difficult terrain, the development of the West was a long and arduous process, and it took centuries." Which choice provides the most effective and concise revision of this sentence? Taken together, these details imply a broader principle that extends beyond the immediate example, though the author stops short of claiming universal proof. Readers must weigh both the evidence presented and the limits the author acknowledges.',
